To find the maximum element in an array of numbers in JavaScript, you can use the `Math.max()` function along with the spread operator (`...`) to pass the elements of the array as individual arguments. Here is an example:

```javascript
function findMaxElement(arr) {
    return Math.max(...arr);
}

const numbers = [3, 5, 7, 2, 8, -1];
const maxElement = findMaxElement(numbers);
console.log(maxElement); // Output: 8
```

In this example, the `findMaxElement` function takes an array as input and returns the maximum value by using `Math.max()` with the spread operator to expand the array elements into individual arguments.
